name: Oldmoss Village
description: In the northwest corner of Oldmoss Village is a slice of ancient woodland claimed long years past and surrounded by the moss dappled palisade that stands there now.   No longer in a time of open war, the gates are never locked and the village is often full of strangers on the road to Cadwell from Minuteâ€™s Harbour.   This tangle of hoary trees and dappled clearnings is home as much to covert merchant meetings as it is to children playing and the many tiny birds that live there.
